House Resolution 818
By: Representatives Bazemore of the 69th, Bennett of the 94th, and Cannon of the 58th
A RESOLUTION
1 Commending the 100 Black Men of South Metro Atlanta and recognizing March 28, 2025,
2 as Community Wellness Day at the Capitol; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, March 28, 2025, is the inaugural Community Wellness Day hosted by the
4 Economic Development of the 100 Black Men of South Metro Atlanta; and
5 WHEREAS, the 100 Black Men of South Metro Atlanta's mission is to empower 5,000
6 community members, with a focus on 500 Black Men, to take control of their health and
7 wellness through comprehensive screenings, education, and resources, while fostering a
8 culture of prevention, early detection, and community support; and
9 WHEREAS, Community Wellness Day will create an environment that saves lives through
10 early detection and prevention; empowers families by providing education, resources, and
11 support; fosters community engagement through partnerships with local businesses,
12 organizations, and healthcare providers; promotes health equality by addressing health
13 disparities and ensuring equal access to healthcare services, education, and resources; and
14 inspires positive change by encouraging individuals to adopt healthy lifestyles; and
