15 WHEREAS, the health and well-being of Georgia's citizens are fundamental to building
16 stronger and more resilient communities; and
17 WHEREAS, the 100 Black Men of South Metro Atlanta have contributed innumerably to the
18 equity, empowerment, and innovation of wellness, making it abundantly fitting and proper
19 that it is appropriately honored.
20 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
21 the members of this body commend the 100 Black Men of South Metro Atlanta for its
22 outstanding contributions to the health and wellness of citizens of the State of Georgia and
23 recognize March 28, 2025, as Community Wellness Day at the Capitol.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
25 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
26 100 Black Men of South Metro Atlanta.
